cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper proposes a method for multi-view clustering using Markov chain based spectral clustering and tensor learning. This involves techniques from machine learning (spectral clustering), artificial intelligence (tensor learning), computer vision (multi-view representation), and statistics (Markov chain). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves optimization techniques (ADMM) and deals with high-dimensional data (tensor), which are relevant to sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
